LAGOS – The Federal Government in its 2022 budget appropriation has made an estimate of N577.36billion for the provision of pension liabilities in 2022. This represents about 3.52per cent of the total budget of N16.39trillion for this year. The breakdown spotted by Daily Independent shows that the military pension and gratuities top the annual budget with N237.77billion; followed by that of the Office of the Head of Service with N36.273billion , while Parastatals and Railway pension will gulp over N30.502billion within the same period. While Department of State Security will have N12.146billion, Custom Services, Immigration and Prison pension office will be saddled with the responsibility of managing the sharing formulae of N8.365billion. NESG Calls For Passage Of Food Safety, Quality Bill Before NASS Role Of Gas As An Enabler Of Energy Transition Other provisions include NEMCO with N31.292billion, Universities Pension including arrears will also consume about N15.537billion and NHIS retirees under military will also share N3.571billion. Also captured in the budget was the provision for Nigerian Intelligence Service with N9.291billion, Police Pension and Gratuities with N8.196billion and DIA civilian staff with N540.7million, the lowest in the provisioning. This is as another N183.8billion was estimated for what the budget office called other pension or miscellaneous provision. Recall that Daily Independent on January 13 this year, reported that the Federal Government had released the sum of N16.67billion earlier released in December 2021, again released the sum of N31.97 billion for the payment of accrued pension rights to 2021 retirees of Treasury-funded Ministries, Departments and Agencies. The total release stood at N48. 64billion. The National Pension Commission (PenCom) in a statement made available to our correspondent had explained that the released funds were for the payment of accrued pension rights under the Contributory Pension Scheme, adding that the sum of N16.67 billion was earlier released in December. The National Pension Commission is pleased to announce an additional release of N31.97 billion by the Federal Government for the payment of accrued pension rights to 2021 retirees of Treasury-funded Ministries, Departments and Agencies. POLL “This follows an earlier release of the sum of N16.67 billion, thus bringing the total amount released for payment of the 2021 accrued pension rights to N48.64 billion.”